ProtoResult:
. "If $\mathbf{X}$ and $\mathbf{Y}$ are in $\R^n$ then 
   \begin{equation} |\mathbf{X}+\mathbf{Y}|\le 
   |\mathbf{X}|+|\mathbf{Y}|, \end{equation} with equality if 
   and only if one of the vectors is a nonnegative multiple of 
   the other."
